com.googlecode.cqengine.index.support
Interface Factory<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
CompoundIndex.DefaultIndexMapFactory, CompoundIndex.DefaultValueSetFactory, DefaultConcurrentSetFactory, HashIndex.DefaultIndexMapFactory, HashIndex.DefaultValueSetFactory, NavigableIndex.DefaultIndexMapFactory, NavigableIndex.DefaultValueSetFactory, UniqueIndex.DefaultIndexMapFactory
public interface Factory<T>

A generic factory for an object of type T.

This is "inspired" by Guava's Supplier or Guice's Provider interface. The purpose of this CQEngine-specific interface is allow a degree of dependency injection/decoupling internally in CQEngine, without imposing a dependency on a particular dependency injection framework on the application.

Author:
Niall Gallagher
